        "description": {
            "value": "<p><strong>Prerequisites</strong> <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.feats-srd\" data-id=\"AimSmPyiMhJZVZRq\" draggable=\"true\"><i class=\"fas fa-suitcase\"></i> Mauler Dedication</a></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong> You’re wielding a non-finesse melee weapon <br>in two hands.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>You smash the ground with your weapon, knocking nearby creatures to the ground.</p>\n<p>Choose a square within your reach, including your own space. If there’s a foe in the chosen square, <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.actionspf2e\" data-id=\"VjxZFuUXrCU94MWR\" draggable=\"true\"><i class=\"fas fa-suitcase\"></i> Strike</a> that foe with the required weapon. Then attempt to <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.actionspf2e\" data-id=\"ge56Lu1xXVFYUnLP\" draggable=\"true\"><i class=\"fas fa-suitcase\"></i> Trip</a> every foe in the chosen square plus each square adjacent to that square, ignoring Trip’s requirement that you have a hand free. This counts as three attacks toward your multiple attack penalty, but the penalty doesn’t increase until after you’ve made the Strike, if any, and all the Trip attempts.</p>",
